Factory method - handles object creation and encapsulates
it in a subclass. This decouples the client code in the
superclass from the object creation code in the subclass.

abstract Product factoryMethod(String type)

abstract - so that subclasses are counted on to handle
object creation
Product - returns a Product that is typically used within
methods defined in the superclass
factoryMethod - isolates the client (the code in the superclass,
like orderPizza()

